data.name: Pulled Pork Sandwiches
data.quickTastyDescription: Tender, flavorful pulled pork served on soft buns, perfect for any casual gathering!
detailedCookingInstructions: Rub the pork shoulder with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and onion powder.
Place the pork shoulder in a slow cooker and pour the barbecue sauce over it.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or high for 4 hours until the pork is tender and easily shredded.
Once cooked, shred the pork using two forks and mix it with the sauce in the slow cooker.
In a bowl, mix coleslaw with apple cider vinegar and sugar to taste.
To assemble, place a generous amount of pulled pork on each hamburger bun and top with coleslaw.
data.detailedName: Slow Cooker Pulled Pork Sandwiches with Coleslaw
